section.def:
hard copy form (印本形式) means a paper
            form or similar form capable of being read without the aid of any equipment;
                (L.N. 222 of 2021)

paragraph.content:
the person is a registered professional surveyor in the building surveying
                    division and complies with
                    paragraph (9);

subparagraph.content:
all site formation works and associated surfacewater drainage works
                        incorporating the requirements of the report prescribed in sub-sub-paragraph
                        (E);

if so required by the Building Authority, specifications and any other
                        relevant particulars;
                        (L.N. 233 of 1982)

a report containing the results of a study including topography,
                        geology, groundwater, surfacewater, site history, public utilities, drains
                        and sewers and other services, and local geotechnical records;

a report containing the results of ground investigation including
                        comprehensive details of equipment and procedures used;
                        (L.N. 233 of 1982)

all excavation and lateral support work (including any ground treatment
                        and any dewatering) incorporating the requirements of the report prescribed
                        in sub-sub-paragraph (E);

a report containing the results of a study including topography,
                        geology, groundwater, surface water, site history, public utilities, water
                        mains, drains and sewers and other services, and local geotechnical records;

paragraph.content:
in respect of any canopy, bridge or other projection over a street or
                    unleased Government land, plans showing clearly the nature and dimension of such projection;
                    (L.N. 79 of 1992; 29 of 1998 s. 105)

a plan showing the construction and condition of the building to be
                    demolished, including sections showing slopes and ground supported by it, and
                    all affected buildings, structures, streets, land and services;

a stability report with calculations demonstrating that the demolition
                    works will not render inadequate the margin of safety of, or cause damage to,
                    any building, structure, street, land and services;

in relation to plans which are submitted for the first time to the Building
                    Authority for approval, 60 days from the date on which the plans were
                    submitted;
